Item: Weblog feed <http://dbaron.org/log/2004-08#e20040830a>

Date: Wed Sep 01 05:48:00 UTC 2004
Author: David Baron

Reading the XSLTused[1] for the newsfeed on the new mozilla.org webpage[2]inspired me to finish a project I started quite a whileago[3]—making an RSS feed for this weblog.  After reading the oneexample XSLT file, I did the rest using only the XSLT spec[4] and theXPath spec[5].So I now have an RSS feed[6] produced by an XSLT transformation sheet[7] (I don't likethe use of the word “stylesheet” for XSLT).  And it'sapparently even valid[8].

Writing it wasn't nearly as bad as I expected, although I am somewhatdisappointed by the inability of XSLT to re-transform trees (i.e., usean already transformed tree, in the form of a resulttree fragment[9] bound to a variable, as the source tree for anadditional transformation).  I worked around the problem using a namedtemplate and xsl:call-template[10].At least I think it's something XSLT can't do—at least I couldn'tsee how in the spec.

